INSERT INTO `B1v12019` VALUES (2,'','0','','ONLINE VERSION','','','','','','',''),(4,'','','','The Building Regulations 2010','','','','','','',''),(5,'','','0.001','','','','','','','',''),(6,'','','','<h2>Fire safety</h2>','','','','','','',''),(7,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(8,'','','','<h2>APPROVED DOCUMENT B</h2>','','','','','','',''),(9,'','','','<h3>Volume 1: Dwellings</h3>','','','','','','',''),(10,'','','','<b>Requirement B1: Means of warning and escape','','','','','','',''),(11,'','','','<b>Requirement B2: Internal fire spread (linings)','','','','','','',''),(12,'','','','<b>Requirement B3: Internal fire spread (structure)','','','','','','',''),(13,'','','','<b>Requirement B4: External fire spread','','','','','','',''),(14,'','','','<b>Requirement B5: Access and facilities for the fire service','','','','','','',''),(15,'','','','<b>Regulations: 6(3), 7(2) and 38</b>','','','','','','',''),(16,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(17,'','','','2019 edition - for use in England. This is an alpha test version. DO NOT USE with live projects','','','','','','',''),(21,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(22,'','','','Main changes in the 2019 edition','','','','','','',''),(23,'','','0.002','This volume of this approved document supports requirements B1 to B5 of Schedule 1 to the','','','','','','',''),(24,'','','','Building Regulations 2010 as well as regulations 6(3), 7(2) and 38. It takes effect on 30 August 2019 for','','','','','','',''),(25,'','','','use in England.','','','','','','',''),(26,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(27,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(28,'','','','The main changes are:','','','','','','',''),(29,'','','0.003','Approved Document B has been redrafted to clarify its language and content in line with the','','','','','','',''),(30,'','','','Department\'s style guide for approved documents. This edition of the approved document','','','','','','',''),(31,'','','','replaces the 2006 edition including all amendments. There are no changes from the previous edition','','','','','','',''),(32,'','','','to the technical guidance within Approved Document B.','','','','','','',''),(33,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(34,'','','','As well as furthering the use of plain English, the document has been significantly restructured:','','','','','','',''),(35,'','','','-   The design of blocks of flats has moved from volume 2 to volume 1.','','','','','','',''),(37,'','','','-   Guidance on the design of sprinkler systems has been consolidated to a new Appendix E.','','','','','','',''),(39,'','','','-   European fire classifications are provided within the main body of the document','','','','','','',''),(40,'','','','with transposition to a national classification provided in Appendix B.','','','','','','',''),(41,'','','','-   The guidance on external stairs has been consolidated.','','','','','','',''),(43,'','','','-   Fire safety information (under regulation 38) has been moved from an appendix','','','','','','',''),(44,'','','','into a new section.','','','','','','',''),(46,'','','','-   The guidance on insulating core panels has moved from an appendix into the Wall','','','','','','',''),(47,'','','','and ceiling linings section.','','','','','','',''),(49,'','','','-   The guidance on fire dampers and ventilation systems has been consolidated.','','','','','','',''),(50,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(54,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(55,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(56,'','','','The approved documents','','','','','','',''),(57,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(58,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(59,'','','','What is an approved document?','','','','','','',''),(60,'','','0.004','The Secretary of State has approved a series of documents that give practical guidance about how','','','','','','',''),(61,'','','','to meet the requirements of the Building Regulations 2010 for England. These approved documents','','','','','','',''),(62,'','','','give guidance on each of the technical parts of the regulations and on regulation 7 (see the back of','','','','','','',''),(63,'','','','this document). The approved documents provide guidance for common building situations.','','','','','','',''),(64,'','','','It is the responsibility of those carrying out building works to meet the requirements of the','','','','','','',''),(65,'','','','Buildings Regulations 2010. Although it is ultimately for the courts to determine whether those','','','','','','',''),(66,'','','','requirements have been met, the approved documents provide practical guidance on potential','','','','','','',''),(67,'','','','ways to achieve compliance with the requirements of the regulations in England.','','','','','','',''),(68,'','','','Although approved documents cover common building situations, compliance with the guidance set','','','','','','',''),(69,'','','','out in the approved documents does not provide a guarantee of compliance with the requirements','','','','','','',''),(70,'','','','of the regulations because the approved documents cannot cater for all circumstances, variations and','','','','','','',''),(71,'','','','innovations. Those with responsibility for meeting the requirements of the regulations will need to','','','','','','',''),(72,'','','','consider for themselves whether following the guidance in the approved documents is likely to meet','','','','','','',''),(73,'','','','those requirements in the particular circumstances of their case.','','','','','','',''),(74,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(75,'','','','Note that there may be other ways to comply with the requirements than the methods described','','','','','','',''),(76,'','','','in an approved document. If you prefer to meet a relevant requirement in some other way than','','','','','','',''),(77,'','','','that described in an approved document, you should seek to agree this with the relevant building','','','','','','',''),(78,'','','','control body at an early stage.','','','','','','',''),(79,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(80,'','','','Where the guidance in the approved document has been followed, a court or inspector will tend','','','','','','',''),(81,'','','','to find that there is no breach of the regulations. However, where the guidance in the approved','','','','','','',''),(82,'','','','document has not been followed, this may be relied upon as tending to establish breach of the','','','','','','',''),(83,'','','','regulations and, in such circumstances, the person carrying out building works should demonstrate','','','','','','',''),(84,'','','','that the requirements of the regulations have been complied with by some other acceptable means','','','','','','',''),(85,'','','','or method.','','','','','','',''),(86,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(87,'','','','In addition to guidance, some approved documents include provisions that must be followed','','','','','','',''),(88,'','','','exactly, as required by regulations or where methods of test or calculation have been prescribed by','','','','','','',''),(89,'','','','the Secretary of State.','','','','','','',''),(90,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(91,'','','','Each approved document relates only to the particular requirements of the Building Regulations','','','','','','',''),(92,'','','','2010 that the document addresses. However, building work must also comply with all other','','','','','','',''),(93,'','','','applicable requirements of the Building Regulations 2010 and all other applicable legislation.','','','','','','',''),(94,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(95,'','','','How to use this approved document','','','','','','',''),(96,'','','0.005','This document uses the following conventions.','','','','','','',''),(97,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(98,'','','','a.  Text against a green background is an extract from the Building Regulations 2010 or the Building','','','','','','',''),(99,'','','','(Approved Inspectors etc.) Regulations 2010 (both as amended). These extracts set out the legal','','','','','','',''),(100,'','','','requirements of the regulations.','','','','','','',''),(101,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(102,'','','','b.  Key terms, printed in green, are defined in Appendix A.','','','','','','',''),(103,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(109,'','','','c.  References are made to appropriate standards or other documents, which can provide further useful','','','','','','',''),(110,'','','','guidance. When this approved document refers to a named standard or other reference document,','','','','','','',''),(111,'','','','the standard or reference document has been clearly identified in this document. Standards are','','','','','','',''),(112,'','','','highlighted in bold throughout. The full name and version of the document referred to is listed in','','','','','','',''),(113,'','','','Appendix F (standards) or Appendix G (other documents). However, if the issuing body has revised or','','','','','','',''),(114,'','','','updated the listed version of the standard or document, you may use the new version as guidance if','','','','','','',''),(115,'','','','it continues to address the relevant requirements of the Building Regulations.','','','','','','',''),(116,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(117,'','','','d.  Standards and technical approvals also address aspects of performance or matters that are not','','','','','','',''),(118,'','','','covered by the Building Regulations and may recommend higher standards than required by the','','','','','','',''),(119,'','','','Building Regulations. Nothing in this approved document precludes you from adopting higher','','','','','','',''),(120,'','','','standards.','','','','','','',''),(121,'','','','User requirements','','','','','','',''),(122,'','','0.006','The approved documents provide technical guidance. Users of the approved documents should','','','','','','',''),(123,'','','','have adequate knowledge and skills to understand and apply the guidance correctly to the building','','','','','','',''),(124,'','','','work being undertaken.','','','','','','',''),(125,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(126,'','','','Where you can get further help','','','','','','',''),(127,'','','0.007','If you are not confident that you possess adequate knowledge and skills to apply the guidance','','','','','','',''),(128,'','','','correctly or if you do not understand the technical guidance or other information in this approved','','','','','','',''),(129,'','','','document or the additional detailed technical references to which it directs you, you should seek','','','','','','',''),(130,'','','','further help. Help can be obtained through a number of routes, some of which are listed below.','','','','','','',''),(131,'','','','a.  If you are the person undertaking the building work: either from your local authority building','','','','','','',''),(132,'','','','control service or from an approved inspector.','','','','','','',''),(134,'','','','b.  If you are registered with a competent person scheme: from the scheme operator.','','','','','','',''),(135,'','','','c.  If your query is technical: from a specialist or an industry technical body for the relevant','','','','','','',''),(136,'','','','subject.','','','','','','',''),(137,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(138,'','ii','','','','','','','','',''),(143,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(144,'','','','The Building Regulations','','','','','','',''),(145,'','','0.008','The following is a high level summary of the Building Regulations relevant to most types of','','','','','','',''),(146,'','','','building work. Where there is any doubt you should consult the full text of the regulations,','','','','','','',''),(147,'','','','available at www.legislation.gov.uk.','','','','','','',''),(148,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(149,'','','','Building work','','','','','','',''),(150,'','','0.009','Regulation 3 of the Building Regulations defines \'building work\'. Building work includes:','','','','','','',''),(151,'','','','a.  the erection or extension of a building','','','','','','',''),(153,'','','','b.  the provision or extension of a controlled service or fitting','','','','','','',''),(154,'','','','c.  the material alteration of a building or a controlled service or fitting.','','','','','','',''),(155,'','','','Regulation 4 states that building work should be carried out in such a way that, when work is','','','','','','',''),(156,'','','','complete:','','','','','','',''),(157,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(158,'','','','a.  For new buildings or work on a building that complied with the applicable requirements of the','','','','','','',''),(159,'','','','Building Regulations: the building complies with the applicable requirements of the Building','','','','','','',''),(160,'','','','Regulations.','','','','','','',''),(161,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(162,'','','','b.  For work on an existing building that did not comply with the applicable requirements of the','','','','','','',''),(163,'','','','Building Regulations:','','','','','','',''),(164,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(165,'','','','i. the work itself must comply with the applicable requirements of the Building Regulations,','','','','','','',''),(166,'','','','and','','','','','','',''),(167,'','','','ii. the building must be no more unsatisfactory in relation to the requirements than before','','','','','','',''),(168,'','','','the work was carried out.','','','','','','',''),(169,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(170,'','','','Material change of use','','','','','','',''),(171,'','','0.010','Regulation 5 defines a \'material change of use\' in which a building or part of a building that was','','','','','','',''),(172,'','','','previously used for one purpose will be used for another.','','','','','','',''),(173,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(174,'','','','The Building Regulations set out requirements that must be met before a building can be used for a','','','','','','',''),(175,'','','','new purpose. To meet the requirements, the building may need to be altered in some way.','','','','','','',''),(176,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(177,'','','','Materials and workmanship','','','','','','',''),(178,'','','0.011','In accordance with regulation 7, building work must be carried out in a workmanlike manner using','','','','','','',''),(179,'','','','adequate and proper materials. Guidance on regulation 7(1) is given in Approved Document 7 and','','','','','','',''),(180,'','','','guidance on regulation 7(2) is provided in Approved Document B.','','','','','','',''),(181,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(182,'','','','Independent third party certification and accreditation','','','','','','',''),(183,'','','0.012','Independent schemes of certification and accreditation of installers can provide confidence that','','','','','','',''),(184,'','','','the required level of performance for a system, product, component or structure can be achieved.','','','','','','',''),(185,'','','','Building control bodies may accept certification under such schemes as evidence of compliance','','','','','','',''),(186,'','','','with a relevant standard. However, a building control body should establish before the start of the','','','','','','',''),(187,'','','','building work that a scheme is adequate for the purposes of the Building Regulations.','','','','','','',''),(188,'','iii','','','','','','','','',''),(194,'','','','Energy efficiency requirements','','','','','','',''),(195,'','','0.013','Part 6 of the Building Regulations imposes additional specific requirements for energy efficiency.','','','','','','',''),(196,'','','','If a building is extended or renovated, the energy efficiency of the existing building or part of it','','','','','','',''),(197,'','','','may need to be upgraded.','','','','','','',''),(198,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(199,'','','','Notification of work','','','','','','',''),(200,'','','0.014','Most building work and material changes of use must be notified to a building control body unless','','','','','','',''),(201,'','','','one of the following applies.','','','','','','',''),(202,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(203,'','','','a.  It is work that will be self-certified by a registered competent person or certified by a registered','','','','','','',''),(204,'','','','third party.','','','','','','',''),(206,'','','','b.  It is work exempted from the need to notify by regulation 12(6A) of, or Schedule 4 to, the','','','','','','',''),(207,'','','','Building Regulations.','','','','','','',''),(208,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(209,'','','','Responsibility for compliance','','','','','','',''),(210,'','','0.015','People who are responsible for building work (e.g. agent, designer, builder or installer) must ensure','','','','','','',''),(211,'','','','that the work complies with all applicable requirements of the Building Regulations. The building','','','','','','',''),(212,'','','','owner may also be responsible for ensuring that work complies with the Building Regulations. If','','','','','','',''),(213,'','','','building work does not comply with the Building Regulations, the building owner may be served','','','','','','',''),(214,'','','','with an enforcement notice.','','','','','','',''),(215,'','iv','','','','','','','','',''),(221,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(222,'','','','Contents','','','','','','',''),(223,'','','0.016','The approved documents','i','','','','','',''),(224,'','','','What is an approved document?','i','','','','','',''),(225,'','','','How to use this approved document','i','','','','','',''),(226,'','','','User requirements','ii','','','','','',''),(227,'','','','Where you can get further help','ii','','','','','',''),(228,'','','','The Building Regulations','iii','','','','','',''),(229,'','','','Section 0: Approved Document B: Fire safety - dwellings','1','','','','','',''),(230,'','','','Summary','1','','','