or better,','','','','','',''),(5954,'','','','-  Any gallery in an assembly building (purpose','which is attached or applied, whether for','','','','','',''),(5955,'','','','group 5).','cladding or any other purpose.','','','','','',''),(5956,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(5957,'','','','-  Any gallery in any other type of building if its','-  Windows, doors or other openings. This does not','','','','','',''),(5958,'','','','area is more than half that of the space into','include windows that are designed and glazed to','','','','','',''),(5959,'','','','which it projects.','give the necessary level of fire resistance and that','','','','','',''),(5960,'','','','-  A roof, unless it is accessible only for','are not openable.','','','','','',''),(5961,'','','','maintenance and repair.','<b>NOTE:</b> Recessed car parking areas as shown in','','','','','',''),(5962,'','','','<b>NOTE:</b> The building is regarded as a multi-storey','Diagram A1 should not be regarded as unprotected','','','','','',''),(5963,'','','','building if both of the following apply.','areas.','','','','','',''),(5964,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(5965,'','','','-  There is more than one gallery.','','','','','','',''),(5966,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(5967,'','','','-  The total aggregate area of all the galleries in','','','','','','',''),(5968,'','','','one space is more than half the floor area of','','','','','','',''),(5969,'','','','that space.','','','','','','',''),(5970,'','117','DiagramA1','','','','','','','',''),(5990,'','118','','','','','','','','',''),(5996,'','','APPB','Appendix B: Performance of materials, products and structures','','','','','','',''),(5997,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(5998,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(5999,'','','','Introduction','','','','','','',''),(6000,'','','AB1','Much of the guidance in this document is given in terms of performance classifications in relation','','','','','','',''),(6001,'','','','to British or European Standards. In such cases, it will be necessary to demonstrate that a system','','','','','','',''),(6002,'','','','or product can meet the relevant performance classification. This will be achieved if the system or','','','','','','',''),(6003,'','','','product complies with one of the following.','','','','','','',''),(6004,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6005,'','','','a.  They should be in accordance with a specification or design that has been shown by a specific','','','','','','',''),(6006,'','','','test to be capable of meeting that performance classification.','','','','','','',''),(6007,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6008,'','','','b.  They should have been designed by using relevant design standards in order to meet that','','','','','','',''),(6009,'','','','performance classification.','','','','','','',''),(6010,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6011,'','','','c.  They should have been assessed by applying relevant test evidence, in lieu of carrying out a','','','','','','',''),(6012,'','','','specific test, as being capable of meeting that performance classification.','','','','','','',''),(6013,'','','','NOTE: Some products are subject to Classification Without Further Testing (CWFT). For the','','','','','','',''),(6014,'','','','purposes of this approved document, such products can be considered to have been shown to be','','','','','','',''),(6015,'','','','capable of meeting a performance specification as per paragraph B1a.','','','','','','',''),(6016,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6017,'','','AB2','Any test evidence used to demonstrate the fire performance classification of a product or system','','','','','','',''),(6018,'','','','should be carefully checked to ensure that it is applicable to the intended use. Small differences','','','','','','',''),(6019,'','','','in detail, such as fixing method, joints, dimensions, the introduction of insulation materials and air','','','','','','',''),(6020,'','','','gaps (ventilated or not), can significantly affect the performance.','','','','','','',''),(6021,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6022,'','','AB3','Assessments should not be regarded as a way to avoid a test where one is necessary. Assessments','','','','','','',''),(6023,'','','','should only be carried out where sufficient relevant test evidence is available. Relevant test','','','','','','',''),(6024,'','','','evidence is unlikely to be provided by test standards which have different classification criteria.','','','','','','',''),(6025,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6026,'','','AB4','Where it is proposed to assess the classification of a product or system in lieu of carrying out a','','','','','','',''),(6027,'','','','specific test (as in paragraph B1b), this should be done in accordance with the relevant standard for','','','','','','',''),(6028,'','','','extended application for the test in question and should include details of the test evidence that','','','','','','',''),(6029,'','','','has been used to support the assessment.','','','','','','',''),(6030,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6031,'','','','For performance classifications where there is no specific standard for extended application,','','','','','','',''),(6032,'','','','assessment reports should be produced in accordance with the principles of BS EN 15725 and','','','','','','',''),(6033,'','','','should include details of the test evidence that has been used to support the assessment. Further','','','','','','',''),(6034,'','','','information on best practice is provided in the Passive Fire Protection Federation\'s Guide to','','','','','','',''),(6035,'','','','Undertaking Assessments in Lieu of Fire Tests.','','','','','','',''),(6036,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6037,'','','','NOTE: Regulation 7(2) limits components used in or on the external walls of certain buildings to','','','','','','',''),(6038,'','','','materials achieving class A2-s1, d0 or class A1 (see Section 10). Assessments cannot be used to','','','','','','',''),(6039,'','','','demonstrate compliance with this requirement.','','','','','','',''),(6040,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6041,'','','AB5','Tests and assessments should be carried out by organisations with the necessary expertise. For','','','','','','',''),(6042,'','','','example, organisations listed as \'notified bodies\' in accordance with the European Construction','','','','','','',''),(6043,'','119','','','','','','','','',''),(6049,'','','','Products Regulation or laboratories accredited by the United Kingdom Accreditation Service (UKAS)','','','','','','',''),(6050,'','','','for the relevant test standard can be assumed to have the necessary expertise.','','','','','','',''),(6051,'','','','NOTE: Standard fire tests do not directly measure fire hazard. They measure or assess the response','','','','','','',''),(6052,'','','','of a material or system to exposure to one or more aspects of fire conditions. Performance in fire','','','','','','',''),(6053,'','','','tests is only one of a number of factors that should be taken into account.','','','','','','',''),(6054,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6055,'','','','Reaction to fire','','','','','','',''),(6056,'','','AB6','Reaction to fire relates to the degree to which a product will contribute, by its own','','','','','','',''),(6057,'','','','decomposition, to a fire under specified conditions. Products, other than floorings, are classified','','','','','','',''),(6058,'','','','as A1, A2, B, C, D, E or F (with class A1 being the highest performance and F being the lowest) in','','','','','','',''),(6059,'','','','accordance with BS EN 13501-1. Class F is assigned when a product fails to attain class E. Untested','','','','','','',''),(6060,'','','','products cannot be classified in accordance with BS EN 13501-1.','','','','','','',''),(6061,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6062,'','','','Materials covered by the Classification Without Further Testing (CWFT) process can be found by','','','','','','',''),(6063,'','','','accessing the European Commission\'s website https://eur-lex.europa.eu/.','','','','','','',''),(6064,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6065,'','','AB7','The classes of reaction to fire performance of A2, B, C, D and E are accompanied by additional','','','','','','',''),(6066,'','','','classifications related to the production of smoke (s1, s2, s3), with s1 indicating the lowest','','','','','','',''),(6067,'','','','production, and/or flaming droplets/particles (d0, d1, d2), with d0 indicating the lowest','','','','','','',''),(6068,'','','','production.','','','','','','',''),(6069,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6070,'','','','NOTE:  When a classification includes s3, d2 this means that there is no limit set for smoke','','','','','','',''),(6071,'','','','production and/or flaming droplets/particles.','','','','','','',''),(6072,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6073,'','','AB8','To reduce the testing burden on manufacturers, BS EN 13238 defines a number of standard','','','','','','',''),(6074,'','','','substrates that produce test results representative of different end use applications. The','','','','','','',''),(6075,'','','','classification for reaction to fire achieved during testing is only valid when the product is used','','','','','','',''),(6076,'','','','within this field of application, i.e. when the product is fixed to a substrate of that class in its','','','','','','',''),(6077,'','','','end use. The standard substrate selected for testing should take account of the intended end use','','','','','','',''),(6078,'','','','applications (field of application) of the product and represent end use substrates that have a','','','','','','',''),(6079,'','','','density of a minimum of 75% of the standard substrate\'s nominal density.','','','','','','',''),(6080,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6081,'','','AB9','Standard substrates include gypsum plasterboard (BS EN 520) with a density of 700+/-100kg/m3,','','','','','','',''),(6082,'','','','calcium silicate board (BS EN 14306) 870+/-50kg/m3 and fibre-cement board 1800+/-200kg/m3.','','','','','','',''),(6083,'','','','NOTE: Standard calcium silicate board is not representative of gypsum plasterboard end use (due','','','','','','',''),(6084,'','','','to the paper layer), but would be representative of most gypsum plasters (with densities of more','','','','','','',''),(6085,'','','','than 650kg/m3).','','','','','','',''),(6086,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6087,'','','','NOTE: Classifications based on tests using a plasterboard substrate would also be acceptable for','','','','','','',''),(6088,'','','','products bonded to a gypsum plaster end use substrate.','','','','','','',''),(6089,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6090,'','','','National classifications for reaction to fire','','','','','','',''),(6091,'','','AB10','This document uses the European classification system for reaction to fire set out in BS EN 13501-1;','','','','','','',''),(6092,'','','','however, there may be some products lawfully on the market using the classification system set','','','','','','',''),(6093,'','','','out in previous editions. Where this is the case, Table B1 can be used for the purposes of this','','','','','','',''),(6094,'','','','document.','','','','','','',''),(6095,'','120','','','','','','','','',''),(6140,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6141,'','','','Thermoplastic materials','','','','','','',''),(6142,'','','AB11','Thermoplastic material is any synthetic polymeric material that has a softening point below 200°C','','','','','','',''),(6143,'','','','if tested to BS EN ISO 306 Method A120. Products formed from these materials cannot always be','','','','','','',''),(6144,'','','','classified in the normal way. In those circumstances the following approach can be followed.','','','','','','',''),(6145,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6146,'','','AB12','Thermoplastic materials used for window glazing, rooflights and lighting diffusers within suspended','','','','','','',''),(6147,'','','','ceilings do not need to meet the criteria within paragraph B19 onwards, if the guidance to','','','','','','',''),(6148,'','','','requirements B2 and B4 is followed.','','','','','','',''),(6149,'','121','','','','','','','','',''),(6155,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6156,'','','AB13','For the purposes of requirements B2 and B4, thermoplastic materials should be classified as TP(a)','','','','','','',''),(6157,'','','','rigid, TP(a) flexible or TP(b), as follows:','','','','','','',''),(6158,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6159,'','','','a. TP(a) rigid','','','','','','',''),(6160,'','','','i. rigid solid uPVC sheet','','','','','','',''),(6161,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6162,'','','','ii. solid (as distinct from double- or multi-skinned) polycarbonate sheet a minimum of 3mm','','','','','','',''),(6163,'','','','thick','','','','','','',''),(6164,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6165,'','','','iii. multi-skinned rigid sheet made from uPVC or polycarbonate that has a class 1 rating when','','','','','','',''),(6166,'','','','tested to BS 476-7','','','','','','',''),(6167,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6168,'','','','iv.  any other rigid thermoplastic product, a specimen of which (at the thickness of the','','','','','','',''),(6169,'','','','product as put on the market), when tested to BS 2782-0 Method 508A, performs so that','','','','','','',''),(6170,'','','','both:','','','','','','',''),(6171,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6172,'','','','-  the test flame extinguishes before the first mark','','','','','','',''),(6173,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6174,'','','','-  the duration of flaming or afterglow does not exceed 5 seconds following removal of','','','','','','',''),(6175,'','','','the burner.','','','','','','',''),(6176,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6177,'','','','b. TP(a) flexible','','','','','','',''),(6178,'','','','Flexible products a maximum of 1mm thick that comply with the Type C requirements','','','','','','',''),(6179,'','','','of BS 5867-2 when tested to BS 5438 Test 2 with the flame applied to the surface of the','','','','','','',''),(6180,'','','','specimens for 5, 15, 20 and 30 seconds respectively, but excluding the cleansing procedure; and','','','','','','',''),(6181,'','','','c. TP(b)','','','','','','',''),(6182,'','','','i. rigid solid polycarbonate sheet products a maximum of 3mm thick, or multi-skinned','','','','','','',''),(6183,'','','','polycarbonate sheet products that do not qualify as TP(a) by test','','','','','','',''),(6184,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6185,'','','','ii. other products which, when a specimen of the material between 1.5 and 3mm thick is','','','','','','',''),(6186,'','','','tested in accordance with BS 2782-0 Method 508A, have a maximum rate of burning of','','','','','','',''),(6187,'','','','50mm/minute.','','','','','','',''),(6188,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6189,'','','','NOTE: If it is not possible to cut or machine a 3mm thick specimen from the product, then a 3mm','','','','','','',''),(6190,'','','','test specimen can be moulded from the same material as that used to manufacture the product.','','','','','','',''),(6191,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6192,'','','AB14','A thermoplastic material alone when used as a lining to a wall or ceiling cannot be assumed to','','','','','','',''),(6193,'','','','protect a substrate. The surface rating of both thermoplastic material and substrate must therefore','','','','','','',''),(6194,'','','','meet the required classification.','','','','','','',''),(6195,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6196,'','','','If, however, the thermoplastic material is fully bonded to a non-thermoplastic substrate, then only','','','','','','',''),(6197,'','','','the surface rating of the composite needs to meet the required classification.','','','','','','',''),(6198,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6199,'','','','Roofs','','','','','','',''),(6200,'','','AB15','Performance of the resistance of roofs to external fire exposure is measured in terms of','','','','','','',''),(6201,'','','','penetration through the roof construction and the spread of flame over its surface.','','','','','','',''),(6202,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6203,'','','AB16','Roof constructions are classified within the European system as BROOF(t4), CROOF(t4), DROOF(t4),','','','','','','',''),(6204,'','','','EROOF(t4) or FROOF(t4) in accordance with BS EN 13501-5. BROOF(t4) indicates the highest performance','','','','','','',''),(6205,'','','','and FROOF(t4) the lowest.','','','','','','',''),(6206,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6207,'','','AB17','BS EN 13501-5 refers to four separate roof tests. The suffix (t4) used in paragraph B16 indicates that','','','','','','',''),(6208,'','','','Test 4 is to be used for the purposes of this approved document.','','','','','','',''),(6209,'','122','','','','','','','','',''),(6215,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6216,'','','AB18','This document uses the European classification system for roof covering set out in','','','','','','',''),(6217,'','','','BS EN 13501-5; however, there may be some products lawfully on the market using the classification','','','','','','',''),(6218,'','','','system set out in previous editions. Where this is the case, Table B2 can be used for the purposes','','','','','','',''),(6219,'','','','of this document.','','','','','','',''),(6220,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6233,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6235,'','','','Fire resistance','','','','','','',''),(6236,'','','AB19','Common to all of the provisions of Part B of the Building Regulations is the property of fire','','','','','','',''),(6237,'','','','resistance. Fire resistance is a measure of one or more of the following.','','','','','','',''),(6238,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6239,'','','','a.  Resistance to collapse (loadbearing capacity), which applies to loadbearing elements only,','','','','','','',''),(6240,'','','','denoted R in the European classification of the resistance to fire performance.','','','','','','',''),(6241,'','','','b.  Resistance to fire penetration (integrity), denoted E in the European classification of the','','','','','','',''),(6242,'','','','resistance to fire performance.','','','','','','',''),(6243,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6244,'','','','c.  Resistance to the transfer of excessive heat (insulation), denoted I in the European','','','','','','',''),(6245,'','','','classification of the resistance to fire performance.','','','','','','',''),(6246,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6247,'','','AB20','The standards of fire resistance necessary for a particular building are based on assumptions about','','','','','','',''),(6248,'','','','the severity of fires and the consequences should an element fail. Fire severity is estimated in very','','','','','','',''),(6249,'','','','broad terms from the use of the building (its purpose group), on the assumption that the building','','','','','','',''),(6250,'','','','contents (which constitute the fire load) are similar for buildings with the same use.','','','','','','',''),(6251,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6252,'','','AB21','Because the use of buildings may change, a precise estimate of fire severity based on the fire load','','','','','','',''),(6253,'','','','due to a particular use may be misleading. Therefore if a fire engineering approach of this kind is','','','','','','',''),(6254,'','','','adopted, the likelihood that the fire load may change in the future needs to be considered.','','','','','','',''),(6255,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6256,'','','AB22','Performance in terms of the fire resistance to be achieved by elements of structure, doors and','','','','','','',''),(6257,'','','','other forms of construction is classified in accordance with one of the following.','','','','','','',''),(6258,'','','','a.  BS EN 13501-2.','','','','','','',''),(6260,'','','','b.  BS EN 13501-3.','','','','','','',''),(6261,'','','','c.  BS EN 13501-4.','','','','','','',''),(6262,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6263,'','','AB23','Fire resistance is measured in minutes. This relates to time elapsed in a standard test and should','','','','','','',''),(6264,'','','','not be confused with real time.','','','','','','',''),(6265,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6266,'','','AB24','The fire resistance necessary for different circumstances is set out in the following tables.','','','','','','',''),(6267,'','123','','','','','','','','',''),(6273,'','','','a.  Table B3 gives the specific requirements for each element of structure.','','','','','','',''),(6274,'','','','b.  Table B4 sets out the minimum periods of fire resistance for elements of structure.','','','','','','',''),(6275,'','','','c.  Table B5 sets out limitations on the use of uninsulated fire resisting glazed elements.','','','','','','',''),(6276,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6277,'','','AB25','This document uses the European classification system for fire resistance set out in BS EN 13501-2','','','','','','',''),(6278,'','','','to 4; however, there may be some products lawfully on the market using the classification system','','','','','','',''),(6279,'','','','set out in previous editions. In those situations the equivalent classifications given in Table B1 can','','','','','','',''),(6280,'','','','be used.','','','','','','',''),(6615,'','130','','','','','','','','',''),(6621,'','','','Application of the fire resistance standards in Table B4','','','','','','',''),(6622,'','','AB26','The following guidance should be used when applying the fire resistance standards in Table B4.','','','','','','',''),(6623,'','','','a. If one element of structure supports or carries or gives stability to another, the fire resistance','','','','','','',''),(6624,'','','','of the supporting element should be no less than the minimum period of fire resistance for the','','','','','','',''),(6625,'','','','other element (whether that other element is loadbearing or not). In some circumstances, it','','','','','','',''),(6626,'','','','may be reasonable to vary this principle, for example:','','','','','','',''),(6627,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6628,'','','','i. if the supporting structure is in the open air and is not likely to be affected by the fire in','','','','','','',''),(6629,'','','','the building','','','','','','',''),(6630,'','','','ii. if the supporting structure is in a different compartment, with a fire-separating element','','','','','','',''),(6631,'','','','(that has the higher standard of fire resistance) between the supporting and the separated','','','','','','',''),(6632,'','','','structure','','','','','','',''),(6633,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6634,'','','','iii. if a plant room on the roof needs greater fire resistance than the elements of structure','','','','','','',''),(6635,'','','','that support it.','','','','','','',''),(6636,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6637,'','','','b. If an element of structure forms part of more than one building or compartment, that element','','','','','','',''),(6638,'','','','should be constructed to the standard of the higher of the relevant provisions.','','','','','','',''),(6639,'','','','c. If, due to the slope of the ground, one side of a basement is open at ground level (allowing','','','','','','',''),(6640,'','','','smoke to vent and providing access for firefighting) for elements of structure in that storey','','','','','','',''),(6641,'','','','it may be appropriate to adopt the standard of fire resistance that applies to above-ground','','','','','','',''),(6642,'','','','structures.','','','','','','',''),(6643,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6644,'','','','d. Although most elements of structure in a single storey building may not need fire resistance,','','','','','','',''),(6645,'','','','fire resistance is needed if one of the following applies to the element.','','','','','','',''),(6646,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6647,'','','','i. It is part of, or supports, an external wall, and there is provision in the guidance on','','','','','','',''),(6648,'','','','requirement B4 to limit the extent of openings and other unprotected areas in the wall.','','','','','','',''),(6649,'','','','ii. It is part of, or supports, a compartment wall, including a wall that is common to two or','','','','','','',''),(6650,'','','','more buildings.','','','','','','',''),(6651,'','','','iii. It supports a gallery.','','','','','','',''),(6652,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6653,'','','AB27','For the purposes of this paragraph, the ground storey of a building that has one or more basement','','','','','','',''),(6654,'','','','storeys and no upper storeys may be considered as a single storey building. The fire resistance of','','','','','','',''),(6655,'','','','the basement storeys should be that specified for basements.','','','','','','',''),(6656,'','131','','','','','','','','',''),(6736,'','133','','','','','','','','',''),(6742,'','','APPC','Appendix C: Fire doorsets','','','','','','',''),(6743,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6744,'','','AC1','All fire doorsets should have the performance shown in Table C1, based on one of the following.','','','','','','',''),(6745,'','','','a.  Fire resistance in terms of integrity, for a period of minutes, when tested to BS 476-22, e.g. FD 30.','','','','','','',''),(6746,'','','','A suffix (S) is added for doorsets where restricted smoke leakage at ambient temperatures is','','','','','','',''),(6747,'','','','needed.','','','','','','',''),(6748,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6749,'','','','b.  As determined with reference to Commission Decision 2000/367/EC regarding the','','','','','','',''),(6750,'','','','classification of the resistance to fire performance of construction products, construction','','','','','','',''),(6751,'','','','works and parts thereof. All fire doorsets should be classified in accordance with BS EN 13501-2,','','','','','','',''),(6752,'','','','tested to the relevant European method from the following.','','','','','','',''),(6753,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6754,'','','','i. BS EN 1634-1.','','','','','','',''),(6755,'','','','ii. BS EN 1634-2.','','','','','','',''),(6756,'','','','iii. BS EN 1634-3.','','','','','','',''),(6757,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6758,'','','','c.  As determined with reference to European Parliament and Council Directive 95/16/EC (which','','','','','','',''),(6759,'','','','applies to lifts that permanently serve buildings and constructions and specified safety','','','','','','',''),(6760,'','','','components) on the approximation of laws of Member States relating to lifts (\'Lifts Directive\')','','','','','','',''),(6761,'','','','implementing the Lifts Regulations 1997 (SI 1997/831) and calling upon the harmonised standard','','','','','','',''),(6762,'','','','BS EN 81-58.','','','','','','',''),(6763,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6764,'','','AC2','The performance requirement is in terms of integrity (E) for a period of minutes. An additional','','','','','','',''),(6765,'','','','classification of Sa is used for all doors where restricted smoke leakage at ambient temperatures is','','','','','','',''),(6766,'','','','needed.','','','','','','',''),(6767,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6768,'','','AC3','The requirement is for test exposure from each side of the doorset separately. The exception is lift','','','','','','',''),(6769,'','','','doors, which are tested from the landing side only.','','','','','','',''),(6770,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6771,'','','AC4','Any test evidence used to verify the fire resistance rating of a doorset or shutter should be','','','','','','',''),(6772,'','','','checked to ensure both of the following.','','','','','','',''),(6773,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6774,'','','','a. It adequately demonstrates compliance.','','','','','','',''),(6775,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6776,'','','','b. It is applicable to the complete installed assembly. Small differences in detail may significantly','','','','','','',''),(6777,'','','','affect the rating.','','','','','','',''),(6778,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6779,'','','','Until relevant harmonised product standards are published, for the purposes of meeting the','','','','','','',''),(6780,'','','','Building Regulations, products tested in accordance with BS EN 1634-1 (with or without pre-fire test','','','','','','',''),(6781,'','','','mechanical conditioning) that achieve the minimum performance in Table C1 will be deemed to','','','','','','',''),(6782,'','','','satisfy the provisions.','','','','','','',''),(6783,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6784,'','','AC5','All fire doorsets, including to flat entrances and between a dwellinghouse and an integral garage,','','','','','','',''),(6785,'','','','should be fitted with a self-closing device, except for all of the following.','','','','','','',''),(6786,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6787,'','','','a.  Fire doorsets to cupboards.','','','','','','',''),(6788,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6789,'','','','b.  Fire doorsets to service ducts normally locked shut.','','','','','','',''),(6790,'','','','c.  Fire doorsets within flats and dwellinghouses.','','','','','','',''),(6791,'','134','','','','','','','','',''),(6797,'','','AC6','If a self-closing device would be considered to interfere with the normal approved use of the','','','','','','',''),(6798,'','','','building, self-closing fire doors may be held open by one of the following.','','','','','','',''),(6799,'','','','a.  A fusible link, but not if the doorset is in an opening provided as a means of escape unless it','','','','','','',''),(6800,'','','','complies with paragraph C7.','','','','','','',''),(6801,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6802,'','','','b.  An automatic release mechanism activated by an automatic fire detection and alarm system.','','','','','','',''),(6803,'','','','c.  A door closer delay device.','','','','','','',''),(6804,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6805,'','','AC7','Two fire doorsets may be fitted in the same opening if each door is capable of closing the opening,','','','','','','',''),(6806,'','','','so the total fire resistance is the sum of their individual resistances. If the opening is provided as a','','','','','','',''),(6807,'','','','means of escape, both fire doorsets should be self-closing.','','','','','','',''),(6808,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6809,'','','','If one fire doorset is capable of being easily opened by hand and has a minimum of 30 minutes\' fire','','','','','','',''),(6810,'','','','resistance, the other fire doorset should comply with both of the following.','','','','','','',''),(6811,'','','','a.  Be fitted with an automatic self-closing device.','','','','','','',''),(6812,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6813,'','','','b.  Be held open by a fusible link.','','','','','','',''),(6814,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6815,'','','AC8','Fire doorsets often do not provide any significant insulation. Unless providing both integrity','','','','','','',''),(6816,'','','','and insulation in accordance with Appendix B, Table B3, a maximum of 25% of the length of a','','','','','','',''),(6817,'','','','compartment wall should consist of door openings.','','','','','','',''),(6818,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6819,'','','','Where it is practicable to maintain a clear space on both sides of the doorway, the above','','','','','','',''),(6820,'','','','percentage may be greater.','','','','','','',''),(6821,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6822,'','','AC9','Rolling shutters should be capable of manual opening and closing for firefighting purposes (see','','','','','','',''),(6823,'','','','Section 15). Rolling shutters across a means of escape should only be released by a heat sensor,','','','','','','',''),(6824,'','','','such as a fusible link or electric heat detector, in the immediate vicinity of the door.','','','','','','',''),(6825,'','','','Unless a shutter is also intended to partially descend as part of a boundary to a smoke reservoir,','','','','','','',''),(6826,'','','','shutters across a means of escape should not be closed by smoke detectors or a fire alarm system.','','','','','','',''),(6827,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6828,'','','AC10','Unless shown to be satisfactory when tested as part of a fire doorset assembly, the essential','','','','','','',''),(6829,'','','','components of any hinge on which a fire door is hung should be made entirely from materials that','','','','','','',''),(6830,'','','','have a minimum melting point of 800°C.','','','','','','',''),(6831,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6832,'','','AC11','Except for doorsets listed in paragraph C12, all fire doorsets should be marked with one of the','','','','','','',''),(6833,'','','','following fire safety signs, complying with BS 5499-5, as appropriate.','','','','','','',''),(6834,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6835,'','','','a.  To be kept closed when not in use - mark \'Fire door keep shut\'.','','','','','','',''),(6836,'','','','b.  To be kept locked when not in use - mark \'Fire door keep locked shut\'.','','','','','','',''),(6837,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6838,'','','','c.  Held open by an automatic release mechanism or free swing device - mark \'Automatic fire door','','','','','','',''),(6839,'','','','keep clear\'.','','','','','','',''),(6840,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6841,'','','','All fire doorsets should be marked on both sides, except fire doorsets to cupboards and service','','','','','','',''),(6842,'','','','ducts, which should be marked on the outside.','','','','','','',''),(6843,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6844,'','','AC12','The following fire doorsets are not required to comply with paragraph C11.','','','','','','',''),(6845,'','','','a.  Doors to and within flats and dwellinghouses.','','','','','','',''),(6846,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6847,'','','','b.  Bedroom doors in \'residential (other)\' (purpose group 2(b)) premises.','','','','','','',''),(6848,'','','','c.  Lift entrance/landing doors.','','','','','','',''),(6849,'','135','','','','','','','','',''),(6855,'','','AC13','The performance of some doorsets set out in Table C1 is linked to the minimum periods of fire','','','','','','',''),(6856,'','','','resistance for elements of structure given in Tables B3 and B4. Limitations on the use of uninsulated','','','','','','',''),(6857,'','','','glazing in fire doorsets are given in Table B5.','','','','','','',''),(6858,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6859,'','','AC14','Recommendations for the specification, design, construction, installation and maintenance of fire','','','','','','',''),(6860,'','','','doorsets constructed with non-metallic door leaves are given in BS 8214.','','','','','','',''),(6861,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6862,'','','','Guidance on timber fire resisting doorsets, in relation to the new European test standard, may be','','','','','','',''),(6863,'','','','found in Timber Fire Resisting Doorsets: Maintaining Performance Under the New European Test','','','','','','',''),(6864,'','','','Standard published by the Timber Research and Development Association (TRADA).','','','','','','',''),(6865,'','','','Guidance for metal doors is given in Code of Practice for Fire Resisting Metal Doorsets published by','','','','','','',''),(6866,'','','','the Door and Shutter Manufacturers\' Association (DSMA).','','','','','','',''),(6867,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6868,'','','AC15','Hardware used on fire doors can significantly affect their performance in a fire. Notwithstanding','','','','','','',''),(6869,'','','','the guidance in this approved document, guidance is available in Hardware for Fire and Escape','','','','','','',''),(6870,'','','','Doors published by the Door and Hardware Federation (DHF) and Guild of Architectural','','','','','','',''),(6871,'','','','Ironmongers (GAI).','','','','','','',''),(6872,'','137','','','','','','','','',''),(6969,'','','APPD','Appendix D: Methods of measurement','','','','','','',''),(6970,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6971,'','','','Occupant number','','','','','','',''),(6972,'','','AD1','The number of occupants of a room, storey, building or part of a building is either of the following.','','','','','','',''),(6973,'','','','a.  The maximum number of people it is designed to hold.','','','','','','',''),(6974,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6975,'','','','b.  In buildings other than dwellings, the number of people calculated by dividing the area of','','','','','','',''),(6976,'','','','a room or storey(s) (m2) by a floor space factor (m2 per person) such as given in Table D1 for','','','','','','',''),(6977,'','','','guidance.','','','','','','',''),(6978,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6979,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6980,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6981,'','','AD2','Counters and display units should be included when measuring area. All of the following should','','','','','','',''),(6982,'','','','be excluded.','','','','','','',''),(6983,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6984,'','','','a.  Stair enclosures.','','','','','','',''),(6985,'','','','b.  Lifts.','','','','','','',''),(6986,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6987,'','','','c.  Sanitary accommodation.','','','','','','',''),(6988,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(6989,'','','','d.  Any other fixed part of the building structure.','','','','','','',''),(6990,'','138','','','','','','','','',''),(7039,'','139','','','','','','','','',''),(7045,'','','','Travel distance','','','','','','',''),(7046,'','','AD3','Travel distance is measured as the shortest route. Both of the following should be observed.','','','','','','',''),(7047,'','','','a.  If there is fixed seating or other fixed obstructions, the shortest route is along the centre line of','','','','','','',''),(7048,'','','','the seatways and gangways.','','','','','','',''),(7049,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7050,'','','','b.  If the route includes a stair, the shortest route is along the pitch line on the centre line of travel.','','','','','','',''),(7051,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7052,'','','DiagramD1','','','','','','','',''),(7053,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7054,'','','','Width','','','','','','',''),(7055,'','','AD4','Width is measured according to the following.','','','','','','',''),(7056,'','','','a.  For a door (or doorway), the clear width when the door is open (Diagram D1).','','','','','','',''),(7057,'','','','b.  For an escape route, either of the following.','','','','','','',''),(7058,'','','','i. When the route is defined by walls: the width at 1500mm above finished floor level.','','','','','','',''),(7059,'','','','ii. Elsewhere: the minimum width of passage available between any fixed obstructions.','','','','','','',''),(7060,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7061,'','','','c.  For a stair, the clear width between the walls or balustrades. On escape routes and stairs,','','','','','','',''),(7062,'','','','handrails and strings intruding into the width by a maximum of 100mm on each side may be','','','','','','',''),(7063,'','','','ignored. Rails used for guiding a stair-lift may be ignored, but it should be possible to park the','','','','','','',''),(7064,'','','','lift\'s chair or carriage in a position that does not obstruct the stair or landing.','','','','','','',''),(7065,'','142','','','','','','','','',''),(7223,'','','DiagramD2','','','','','','','',''),(7224,'','','DiagramD3','','','','','','','',''),(7225,'','','DiagramD4','','','','','','','',''),(7226,'','','DiagramD5','','','','','','','',''),(7227,'','','DiagramD6','','','','','','','',''),(7228,'','','DiagramD7','','','','','','','',''),(7229,'','143','','','','','','','','',''),(7232,'','','','Free area of smoke ventilators','','','','','','',''),(7233,'','','AD5','The free area of a smoke ventilator should be measured by either of the following.','','','','','','',''),(7234,'','','','a.  The declared aerodynamic free area in accordance with BS EN 12101-2.','','','','','','',''),(7235,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7236,'','','','b.  The total unobstructed cross-sectional area (geometric free area), measured in the plane where','','','','','','',''),(7237,'','','','the area is at a minimum and at right angles to the direction of air flow (Diagram D7).','','','','','','',''),(7238,'','144','','','','','','','','',''),(7254,'','','APPE','Appendix E: Sprinklers','','','','','','',''),(7255,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7256,'','','','Sprinkler systems','','','','','','',''),(7257,'','','AE1','Sprinkler systems installed in buildings can reduce the risk to life and significantly reduce the','','','','','','',''),(7258,'','','','degree of damage caused by fire within a building.','','','','','','',''),(7259,'','','AE2','Further recommendations for the provision of sprinklers are provided in the following sections:','','','','','','',''),(7287,'','145','','','','','','','','',''),(7290,'','','','Design of sprinkler systems','','','','','','',''),(7291,'','','AE3','Where required, sprinkler systems should be provided throughout the building or separated part,','','','','','','',''),(7292,'','','','unless acting as a compensatory feature to address a specific risk. They should be designed and','','','','','','',''),(7293,'','','','installed in accordance with the following.','','','','','','',''),(7294,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7295,'','','','a.  For residential buildings, the requirements of BS 9251.','','','','','','',''),(7296,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7297,'','','','b.  For non-residential buildings, or residential buildings outside the scope of BS 9251, the','','','','','','',''),(7298,'','','','requirements of BS EN 12845, including the relevant hazard classification together with','','','','','','',''),(7299,'','','','additional measures to improve system reliability and availability as described in Annex F of the','','','','','','',''),(7300,'','','','standard.','','','','','','',''),(7301,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7302,'','','','NOTE: Any sprinkler system installed to satisfy the requirements of Part B of the Building','','','','','','',''),(7303,'','','','Regulations should be provided with additional measures to improve system reliability and','','','','','','',''),(7304,'','','','availability and is therefore to be regarded as a life safety system. However, there may be some','','','','','','',''),(7305,'','','','circumstances in which additional measures to improve system reliability and availability specified','','','','','','',''),(7306,'','','','in Annex F of BS EN 12845 are inappropriate or unnecessary.','','','','','','',''),(7307,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7308,'','','AE4','If the provisions in a building vary from those in this document, sprinkler protection can also','','','','','','',''),(7309,'','','','sometimes be used as a compensatory feature.','','','','','','',''),(7310,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7311,'','','','BS 9251 makes additional recommendations when sprinklers are proposed as compensatory features.','','','','','','',''),(7312,'','','','Water supplies and pumps','','','','','','',''),(7313,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7314,'','','AE5','For non-residential sprinkler systems designed and installed to BS EN 12845, water supplies should','','','','','','',''),(7315,'','','','consist of either of the following.','','','','','','',''),(7316,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7317,'','','','a.  Two single water supplies complying with clause 9.6.1, independent of each other.','','','','','','',''),(7318,'','','','b.  Two stored water supplies meeting all of the following conditions.','','','','','','',''),(7319,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7320,'','','','i. Gravity or suction tanks should satisfy all the requirements of clause 9.6.2(b), other than','','','','','','',''),(7321,'','','','capacity.','','','','','','',''),(7322,'','','','ii. Any pump arrangements should comply with clause 10.2.','','','','','','',''),(7323,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7324,'','','','iii. In addition to meeting the requirements for inflow, either of the following should apply.','','','','','','',''),(7325,'','','','-  The capacity of each tank should be at least half the specified minimum water volume','','','','','','',''),(7326,'','','','of a single full capacity tank, appropriate to the hazard.','','','','','','',''),(7327,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7328,'','','','-  One tank should be at least equivalent to half the specified water volume of a single','','','','','','',''),(7329,'','','','full capacity tank, and the other shall not be less than the minimum volume of a','','','','','','',''),(7330,'','','','reduced capacity tank (see clause 9.3.4) appropriate to the hazard.','','','','','','',''),(7331,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7332,'','','','The total capacity of the water supply in (iii), including any inflow for a reduced capacity','','','','','','',''),(7333,'','','','tank, should be at least that of a single full holding capacity tank that complies with Table','','','','','','',''),(7334,'','','','9, Table 10 or clause 9.3.2.3, as appropriate to the hazard and pipework design.','','','','','','',''),(7335,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7336,'','','AE6','For the systems described in paragraph E5, both of the following apply if pumps are used to draw','','','','','','',''),(7337,'','','','water from two tanks.','','','','','','',''),(7338,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7339,'','','','a.  Each pump should be able to draw water from either tank.','','','','','','',''),(7340,'','','','b.  Any one pump, or either tank, should be able to be isolated.','','','','','','',''),(7341,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7342,'','','','The sprinkler water supplies should not be used as connections for other services or other fixed','','','','','','',''),(7343,'','','','firefighting systems.','','','','','','',''),(7344,'','146','','','','','','','','',''),(7350,'','','APPF','Appendix F: Standards referred to','','','','','','',''),(7351,'','','','','','','','','','',''),(7352,'','','','<h4>European Standards</h4>','<b>BS EN 1634</b> Fire resistance and smoke control tests','','','','','',''),(7353,'','','','','for door and shutter assemblies, openable windows','','','','','',''),(7354,'','','','<b>NOTE:</b> All the British and European Standards can','and elements of building hardware','','','','','',''),(7355,'','','','be purchased at the following address: https://','<b>BS EN 1634-1</b> Fire resistance test for door and','','','','','',''),(7356,'','','','shop.bsigroup.com/. Alternatively access to the','shutter assemblies and openable windows [2014','','','','','',''),(7357,'','','','British and European Standards may be gained at','+ A1 2018]','','','','','',''),(7358,'','','','public reference libraries.','','','','','','',''),(7359,'','','','','<b>BS EN 1634-2</b> Fire resistance characterisation test','','','','','',''),(7360,'','','','<b>BS EN 54</b> Fire detection and fire alarm systems','for elements of building hardware [2008]','','','','','',''),(7361,'','','','<b>BS EN 54-7</b> Smoke detectors. Point smoke','<b>BS EN 1634-3</b> Smoke control test for door and','','','','','',''),(7362,'','','','detectors that operate using scattered light,','shutter assemblies [2004]','','','','','',''),(7363,'','','','transmitted light or ionization [2018]','','','','','','',''),(7364,'','','','','<b>BS EN 1993-1-2</b> Eurocode 3. Design of steel','','','','','',''),(7365,'','','','<b>BS EN 54-11</